title: Germany's Ludwig, Walkenhorst win FIVB Puerto Vallarta Open
text:
Germany’s Ludwig, Walkenhorst win FIVB Puerto Vallarta Open By - Associated Press - Sunday, October 11, 2015 
PUERTO VALLARTA, Mexico (AP) - Germany’s Laura Ludwig and Kira Walkenhorst won the season-opening FIVB Puerto Vallarta Open on Sunday, beating Brazil’s Eduarda Lisboa and Elize Maia 21-18, 21-16. 
Ludwig and Walkenhorst have combined for three FIVB international titles. 
Americans Nick Lucena and Phil Dalhausser beat the Netherlands’ Alexander Brouwer and Robert Meeuwsen 21-12, 21-18 in the men’s final. In eight FIVB international events as a team Lucena and Dalhausser have two titles and three runner-up finishes. Dalhausser has 31 career victories.
